City Hall is a 1996 film directed by Harold Becker. It stars Al Pacino, John Cusack and Bridget Fonda. The plot follows the aftermath of the death of a boy caught in the crossfire of a shootout between a drug dealer and a detective.According to the website Box Office Mojo, the film grossed an estimated $20 million in the U.S.This was Becker's second collaboration with Pacino, having directed him in Sea of Love released seven years earlier.
